(1, '9649', '2019-10-09 04:42:32', 'с 1999 года', 'Adventure Fiction, Fantasy', '<p> The action takes place in the fictional and only continent on the planet Red Line. It encircles the world around its entire diameter and serves as a refuge for fantastic creatures. In addition to the usual people, here you can meet mermaids, giants, as well as magical anomalies. The two oceans perpendicular to the mainland are divided by the Grand Line, where the laws of physics differ. Experienced sailors to replace the ordinary compass adapted the invention of \"log-pos\", which allows you to navigate the terrain. Technological progress froze in place and is similar to the European XVII century. Outlandish methods of solving problems are widely used here, and cochlear-shaped animals connected to the network carry out communication. </p> <p> The Red Line is entirely led by the World Government, but there are also a number of independent organizations fighting for fair power and the equality of the people. The most progressive political player is the Revolutionary Movement, which has gathered millions of like-minded people in its army. Thanks to their subversive activities, a number of cities escaped from the yoke of totalitarianism. Oceanic spaces are divided into three factions: the government organization Marine Watch, fulfilling privateer obligations of the Seven Great Corsairs and the freedom-loving Four Emperors of the Seas. After the execution of the Pirate King Gold Roger, who hid the untold wealth of Van Pease in an unknown place, an unbridled race among adventurers looking for a treasure begins. The plot follows a thin guy in a straw hat Monkey D. Luffy, dreaming of a great pirate future. </p>', '/image/OnePiece.jpg', '<a href=\"http://localhost:8080/home/anime?page=OnePiece&chapter=embed/9649/&season=1&seria=1#videoPlayer\"><button class=\"bp-q\"> Series 1</button></a>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8080/home/anime?page=OnePiece&chapter=embed/9649/&season=1&seria=2#videoPl