(3, '13814', '2019-10-09 04:42:32', '2004', 'Drama, Comedy, Mystery, Adventure, Shonen, Fantasy, School, Multi-Series', '<p> As far as I remember, Ichigo Kurosaki sees spirits. He lost his mother early and lives with his father and two sisters. After meeting with the Shinigami, a spirit girl in a black kimono and with a sword, which is a guide of souls, his life changed dramatically. She fought with monsters and sent spirits to the other world for a long time. But during the next battle that happened in front of Ichigo, she was wounded and realized that she could not defeat the monster, which means that not only she, but Ichigo and his two sisters would die, so she decided to transfer her powers to him. So Ichigo gained strength by the Shinigami and can now see monstrous spirits and kill them with a huge sword, and send restless spirits to Paradise or Hell with the other end of his sword. </p> <p> Ichigo is a guy with a character, he does not want to take all the duties of the Shinigami, he wants to continue his former life - go to the old school, live with his stern father, who works in the hospital. But the Shinigami of Rukia Kuchiki, from whom he took power, gained a human face and came to study in his class to be closer to him and teach everything that she knows. Monsters continue to attack Ichigo day and night and it is not always easy for him to cope with them. All these monsters were once human before, and now they have become \"Empty\" of their own free will, or because they were influenced by other \"Empty\", the purpose of which is to capture the souls of the restless. Not always in their previous lives they were bad people, and Ichigo, having looked at the faces of the monsters with whom he has to fight, can even recognize someone from those who died in his district ... </p>', '/image/Bleach.jpg', '<a href=\"http://localhost:8080/home/anime?page=Bleach&chapter=embed/13814/&season=1&seria=1#videoPlayer\"><button class=\"bp-q\"> Series 1</button></a> <a hre